
// Narrative: starts with a quoted portion (same line)
"Madness!" she cried.

// Narrative: quoted start + continuation on next line (paragraph combining)
"This is fine."
she said calmly.

// Narrative: quote in the middle (already worked)
She asked "why?" and ran.

// Narrative: quote at end (already worked)
He said "this is madness!"

// Dialogue: quoted portion at start of inline text
barista: "Try the latte!" she suggested.

// Dialogue: quote at end (already worked)
barista: She said "try the latte".

// Dialogue: multiline with quoted start + continuation
barista: "It's the best!" he exclaimed.
  I totally agree.

// Dialogue: quoted-only first line + continuation
barista: "It's the best!"
  I totally agree.

// Unquoted assign with embedded quotes
state
  label: nothing

label := "wow" that is neat
"Label: $label"

// Standalone quoted strings remain unchanged
"This is still a proper quoted string."

// Escaped opening quote makes the whole line unquoted
\"This will be displayed with the double quotes included."

